[SN]TITLE[SN]
What stories should African novelists tell?

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
One of Nigeria's biggest cultural events is under way in the city Abeokuta. Now in its fourth year, the five-day Ake Arts and Book festival attracts well-known writers from across the continent.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
19 November 2016 Last updated at 00:16 GMT
The BBC's Martin Patience asked some of them what stories needed to be told in Africa today.
